Btw, My favorite API for hijacking a connection in Pluto would be something like:
```# In julia
register_plugin("jsserve") do client_session, message_raw_bytes
   JSServe.process(client_session.id, message)
end
# in js:
function jsserve_init() {
    Pluto.register_plugin("jsserve", (conn_to_sent_raw_bytes) =&gt; {
       // Make sure JSServe is using Plutos websocket connection - pluto will need to attach a client id + session to this on the julia side 
       JSServe.global_connection[] = conn_to_sent_raw_bytes
        return function on_message(message_raw_bytes) { 
             JSServe.handle_message(message_raw_bytes)
        }
    })
}```

